Posts.Content: Apr 11, 2007 05:57PM Tamodeez wrote: I also have dense breast tissue in my left breast. Had a digital mammo done with an ultrasound. Both came up normal or saying they didn't see anything, but to come back in 6 months. Went to my breast surgeon who say my right breast actually felt fuller to her. Anyways, just to ease my mind about that dreaded "hiding cancer" in dense breast tissue and so I wouldn't have to come back in 6 months, my dr. ordered a MRI. I had it done yesterday. I'm still waiting for the results and hope they come back clear. What I do know is that digital mammograms and ultrasounds do a good job, but MRI can find very small cancers, but they also find things that aren't cancer. Even though I'm anxious waiting for the results, I"m glad I had it done. Even if they do find something, I'm hoping it will be small and curable.
